      <abstract>
        <p>April 10 article about The Diary of Petr Ginz: 1941-1942 omitted translator of untitled poem in book that was quoted in article; he is David Curzon</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An article in The Arts on Tuesday about ''The Diary of Petr Ginz: 1941-1942,'' a teenager's chronicle of life in wartime Prague, omitted a translator of an untitled poem in the book that was quoted in the article. While Elena Lappin translated the book from the Czech, David Curzon helped her translate that poem and another in the book called ''Remembering Prague.''</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
